Orlovo Climate Summary

Located at an elevation of None meters (0 feet) above sea level, Orlovo has a Subartic, severe winter, no dry season, cool summer climate (Classification: Dfc). The district’s yearly temperature is 1.19ºC (34.14ºF) and it is -4.08% lower than Russia’s averages. Orlovo typically receives about 96.87 millimeters (3.81 inches) of precipitation and has 176.58 rainy days (48.38% of the time) annually.
